<script type="text/javascript" src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">// <![CDATA[</p>
<p>// ]]&gt;</script><br />
For adults and older children, appropriate rest and plenty of liquids are important parts of the recovery regimen. For babies or younger children, treatment will include isolation from others to prevent transmission between babies. Unfortunately, cough medicines are often ineffective in the face of pertussis and may not offer relief of the symptoms. All prescribed antibiotics should be taken until finished even if symptoms are diminished or gone. The doctor should be contacted immediately if seizures, troubled breathing, high fever, or hernias occur. If the infected person is unable to keep food down, an intravenous line may be used.</p>
